[[File:Concordance_of_Fealty.jpg|thumb|Concordance of Fealty between Eeth Koth and Mace Windu]]
{{Quote|Master Eeth Koth, I have something to return to you. It is a product of your own hands which you once entrusted to mine. In returning this lightsaber, I return your trust.|Mace Windu|<ref name="SW13">[[Star Wars (1998) 13|''Star Wars'' (1998) 13]]</ref>}}
The '''Concordance of Fealty''' was the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] tradition of exchanging one's [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] with that of a fellow member of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]. This exchange was considered a sacred bond, symbolizing mutual trust. The tradition included a vow of [[reciprocal apprenticeship]],<ref name="Skye">''[[SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story]]''</ref> though this facet was little practiced after the [[Cleansing of the Nine Houses]],<ref name="DFS">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20050407a|series=The Dark Forces Saga|text=Part 1}}</ref> a conflict of the [[Old Sith Wars]],<ref name="HotM">{{InsiderCite|80|The History of the Mandalorians: Exploring the Evolution of a Mighty Race of Warriors}}</ref> and was generally undertaken only by [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]].<ref name="Skye" />

[[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi Councilors]] [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]] and [[Eeth Koth]] completed the Concordance of Fealty shortly prior to Windu's departure on a [[Lannik–Red Iaro peace negotiations|diplomatic mission]] to negotiate peace between the [[R'cardo Sooflie IX|prince]] of the [[Lannik (species)/Legends|Lannik people]] and the [[Red Iaro/Legends|Red Iaro]] [[Terrorist/Legends|terrorists]],<ref name="SW13" /> approximately [[32 BBY/Legends|32 years before]] the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]].<ref name="Omni">''[[Star Wars Omnibus: Emissaries and Assassins]]''</ref>

In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="SWDate">''[[SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story]]'' takes place during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] and prior to [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker's]] knighting. ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates both the beginning of the Clone Wars and Skywalker's knighting to [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], and ''SkyeWalkers'' must therefore take place in the same [[Standard year/Legends|year]].</ref> [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] and [[Halagad Ventor]] engaged in the Concordance of Fealty, unusually for [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] apprentices, during a [[Battle of Skye|mission]] to the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Skye/Legends|Skye]]. Due to their exchange of lightsabers,<ref name="Skye" /> [[S'kytri|Skye native]] [[Aragh]], in a later account to [[Rebel pilot/Legends|Rebel pilot]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], would identify the two Jedi pupils as the fallen Jedi Darth Vader, and the bearer of the [[Anakin Skywalker's second lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] belonging to Skywalker's father<ref name="SWA1">[[Star Wars Annual (1977) 1|''Star Wars Annual'' (1977) 1]]</ref> Anakin, despite the fact that Vader and the elder Skywalker were in fact one and the same.<ref name="TESB">{{Film|V}}</ref>

On a 22 BBY mission to locate his former Padawan Jedi Master [[Depa Billaba/Legends|Depa Billaba]] on his [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] [[Haruun Kal/Legends|Haruun Kal]],<ref name="TERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref> Mace Windu discovered Billaba's lightsaber in the posession of local guide [[Nick Rostu]]. Speculating on how Rostu acquired the [[Weapon/Legends|weapon]], Windu mused that it was unlikely to have been a Concordance of Fealty.<ref name="Shatterpoint">[[Shatterpoint (novel)|''Shatterpoint'']]</ref>

During the reign of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], former [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hand]] [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] and [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Kyle Katarn]] were engaged in the reciprocal apprenticeship facet of the Concordance of Fealty.<ref name="DFS" />

==Known participants==
*[[Eeth Koth/Legends|Eeth Koth]] and [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]]<ref name="SW13" />
*[[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] and [[Halagad Ventor]]<ref name="Skye" />
*[[Kyle Katarn]] and [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]]<ref name="DFS" />

==Behind the scenes==
The tradition of the Concordance of Fealty was created as a [[Retroactive continuity|retcon]] to explain the difference between Mace Windu's two lightsabers, the one that appears in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']], and the one that comes with the [[Hasbro]] action figure. It was later used to explain the description of the [[Battle of Skye]] in [[Star Wars Annual (1977) 1|''Star Wars Annual'' (1977) 1]] that implies [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] and Darth Vader to be separate people by differentiating between Darth Vader and the Jedi who wore the lightsaber worn by [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. In ''[[Star Wars Gamer]]'' and ''[[Aliens in the Empire]]'', it was explained that [[Halagad Ventor]] and Anakin Skywalker had temporarily switched lightsabers for the Concordance of Fealty.

